data.description: This charming 4 bed 2 bath house is the perfect first home. It is centrally located with easy walking/cycling access to all the main attractions of Stevens Point. When you own this home, feel free to just leave the car in the garage and experience beautiful Stevens Point. If you're not feeling up for outdoor activities, make a meal in the spacious kitchen with a professional hood, stainless steel farmhouse sink and a gas range. The front porch is perfect for those that want to relax and read a book or watch the traffic go by. The home also features a lot of character with wood floors and built in wood fixtures and cabinetry. Buyers in the North Point area really focus on these features!,The major updates include a newer furnace, water heater and central AC, vented oven hood, complete gutter system and Nest Thermostat. The basement features a packed and sealed stone foundation and a new 2" concrete floor with a perimeter channel and PVC conduits running to the drain. This home offers quick access to Sentry Insurance, SentryWorld, the Downtown Business District, Midstate Technical College and University of Wisconsin Stevens Point Campuses.
